abstract":[{"text":"HealthKit is an essential framework that integrates first- and third-party health and fitness data to help people manage their personal health information. Learn about HealthKit’s latest updates, which provide read access to electrocardiograms on Apple Watch and log and track over a dozen new symptoms and their severity. We’ll also go through the latest mobility data types like walking speed and step length to help people monitor and understand their mobility over time.","type":"text"}],"metadata":{"role":"sampleCode","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"roleHeading":"WWDC20","title":"What’s new in HealthKit"},"references":{"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC20-10184-Synchronize-health-data-with-HealthKit":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10184-Synchronize-health-data-with-HealthKit","role":"sampleCode","abstract":[{"text":"HealthKit provides you the tools to smartly manage health data anywhere, whether across multiple HealthKit-enabled devices such as iPhone and Apple Watch or with an external server to share data across a care team. In this session, we’ll dive into managing data versions via HealthKit’s built-in sync identifier metadata, how to detect changes in health data using an HKAnchoredObjectQuery, and cover best practices for ensuring you’re always working with the right data everywhere.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","title":"Synchronize health data with HealthKit","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10184-synchronize-health-data-with-healthkit","type":"topic"},"https://github.com/mike011":{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/mike011","type":"link","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mike011","title":"GitHub","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"GitHub","type":"text"}]},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/healthkit/hkelectrocardiogram/3551983-samplingfrequency":{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/healthkit\/hkelectrocardiogram\/3551983-samplingfrequency","type":"link